<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News]]></title><link/> https://sputniknews.com/新闻<atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/sputniknews" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RSSHub</generator><webmaster> i@diygod.me (DIY神)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 5 月 20 日星期六 05:26:29 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[White House Says Has Serious Differences With Republicans on Debt Limit Talks]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110476281" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/09/1110211152_0:0:2653:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_a7c346bec9218c21572787a177f223f3.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1110211134" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/white-house-says-has-serious-differences-with-republicans-on-debt-limit-talks-1110476281.html?share-img=1110211134"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / DANIEL SLIM</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">白宫于 2022 年 5 月 19 日在华盛顿特区亮相</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="The White House is seen on May 19, 2022 in Washington, DC - Sputnik International, 1920, 20.05.2023" title="白宫于 2022 年 5 月 19 日在华盛顿特区亮相" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/09/1110211152_0:278:2653:1770_1920x0_80_0_0_fdde1c596abf5ab7924a76d780a09d85.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/09/1110211152_0:278:2653:1770_640x0_80_0_0_4cb5d379a141f61dfd005978d0a72360.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/09/1110211152_0:278:2653:1770_1280x0_80_0_0_e1d307a4dd64923005823e821e76e96d.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/09/1110211152_0:278:2653:1770_1920x0_80_0_0_fdde1c596abf5ab7924a76d780a09d85.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / 丹尼尔斯利姆</div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据华盛顿（人造卫星）网报道：白宫新闻秘书卡琳·让-皮埃尔在新闻发布会上说，美国总统乔·拜登的白宫与共和党国会领导人在正在进行的债务限制谈判中存在严重分歧。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “毫无疑问，我们存在严重分歧，这将继续成为一个问题，”让-皮埃尔周五表示。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">让-皮埃尔补充说，白宫对就提高<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230515/us-consumer-debt-stands-at-17-trillion-credit-card-defaults-at-pandemic-level-1110385817.html" target="_blank">美国债务上限</a>达成协议充满信心和乐观。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">白宫国家安全顾问杰克沙利文在一次会议上表示，正在进行的提高美国债务上限和避免迫在眉睫的违约谈判是日本七国集团 (G7) 峰会的一个关注主题，尽管此事并未引起恐慌新闻发布会。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “[美国债务上限]绝对是七国集团感兴趣的话题......这不会在房间内引起恐慌或某种震动，”沙利文周五表示。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110476281" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/white-house-says-has-serious-differences-with-republicans-on-debt-limit-talks-1110476281.html?share-block=1110476285" data-title="&quot;[The US debt ceiling] is definitely a subject of interest here at the G7… This is not generating alarm or a kind of vibration in the room,&quot; Sullivan said on Friday."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">沙利文补充说，美国总统乔·拜登表示有信心，他相信在回国与国会领导人进行谈判后，他可以“推动”达成避免违约的结果。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国总统拜登和共和党议员目前正在进行谈判，以期在美国政府最早于 6 月面临违约风险之前达成提高债务上限的协议。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">债务上限谈判已持续数月，但仅在最近几周才愈演愈烈，双方似乎都在为即将达成的协议采取一些行动；但是，尚未得到官方确认。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 04:39:48 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/white-house-says-has-serious-differences-with-republicans-on-debt-limit-talks-1110476281.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/white-house-says-has-serious-differences-with-republicans-on-debt-limit-talks-1110476281.html<category>美洲</category><category>我们</category><category>卡琳·让-皮埃尔</category><category>乔·拜登</category><category>白色的房子</category><category>美国债务上限危机</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Pat-S’ Self-Propelled Howitzer Getting Revived in Russia - Developer]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110476109" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102686/71/1026867112_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_3612c2f78d5823b56d1e13f029b3f61e.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1026867111" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/pat-s-self-propelled-howitzer-getting-revived-in-russia---developer-1110476109.html?share-img=1026867111"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Anton Denisov</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">BMP-3 战车</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="BMP-3 combat vehicle - Sputnik International, 1920, 20.05.2023" title="BMP-3战车" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102686/71/1026867112_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_354ffd7dc9f49155e5b8914236f56947.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102686/71/1026867112_0:160:3072:1888_640x0_80_0_0_8d20c7864436adb8855230adc6c72bfa.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102686/71/1026867112_0:160:3072:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_a09d07847bc730d62396d99b8972e519.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102686/71/1026867112_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_354ffd7dc9f49155e5b8914236f56947.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / 安东杰尼索夫</div>/ </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据莫斯科（人造卫星）网报道：Kurganmashzavod 制造公司是俄罗斯国有国防公司 Rostec 的一部分，该公司发言人告诉人造卫星，该公司正在致力于对 152 毫米“Pat-S”自行火炮装置进行现代化改造。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “基于改进的 BMP-3 [步兵战车] 底盘的自行<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230514/watch-russias-akatsiya-artillery-system-performs-combat-work-during-special-op-1110335623.html" target="_blank">火炮</a>装置的现代化正在进行中。这些车辆配备了 120 毫米火炮……和 152 毫米火炮，能够显着提高机动步枪部队，”发言人说。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “Pat-S”是一种试验性的 152 毫米自行火炮炮架，于 1980 年代在苏联开发，基于 BMP-3 底盘。它没有量产，只制造了一个原型。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “Pat-S”是世界上第一款能够自行漂浮克服水障碍的大口径榴弹炮。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 04:23:40 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/pat-s-self-propelled-howitzer-getting-revived-in-russia---developer-1110476109.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/pat-s-self-propelled-howitzer-getting-revived-in-russia---developer-1110476109.html<category>军队</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>BMP-3</category><category>俄罗斯技术集团公司</category><category>榴弹炮</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ecuador’s President Says He Won’t Seek Reelection After Disbanding Legislature]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110475449" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/08/0e/1099592899_0:0:1582:882_1440x900_80_0_1_7f039a27db3c3ed840b19b9e92b8c7f0.png?source-sid=" data-photoview-image-id="1099592882" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/ecuadors-president-says-he-wont-seek-reelection-after-disbanding-legislature-1110475449.html?share-img=1099592882"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"><span class="photoview__copyright"></span><span class="photoview__desc-text">厄瓜多尔总统吉列尔莫·拉索在军事仪式上</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="" alt="Ecuadorian President Guillermo Lasso at a Military Ceremony - Sputnik International, 1920, 20.05.2023" title="厄瓜多尔总统吉列尔莫·拉索在军事仪式上" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/08/0e/1099592899_7:0:1575:882_1920x0_80_0_0_8dee6fe1908ae44081ea1953f0c05055.png" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/08/0e/1099592899_7:0:1575:882_640x0_80_0_0_3c3f78a6a9b232adf8a795d9b5e84ebf.png 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/08/0e/1099592899_7:0:1575:882_1280x0_80_0_0_c740fc02bdfcf66751d8907b7044370e.png 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/08/0e/1099592899_7:0:1575:882_1920x0_80_0_0_8dee6fe1908ae44081ea1953f0c05055.png 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">伊恩德马蒂诺</div><div class="article__author-links"> <a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_demartino_ian/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">周三，厄瓜多尔总统吉列尔莫·拉索宣布解散该国立法机构，并将在 90 天内举行新的选举。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在为避免弹劾投票而解散国民议会几天后，厄瓜多尔总统吉列尔莫·拉索表示他不会参加他的举动现在提示的即将举行的特别选举，并补充说他不在乎谁接替他的职位。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “我的目​​标不是阻止某人返回厄瓜多尔，”拉索对美国媒体说，他指的是流亡比利时但在厄瓜多尔政坛仍有很大影响力的前总统拉斐尔·科雷亚。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> <strong>Lasso 根据厄瓜多尔宪法第 148 条使用了一种名为 muerte cruzada 或“cross-death”的工具。此举解散了该国的国民议会，但还要求在 90 天内举行新的议会和总统选举。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Lasso 面临贪污和腐败指控，他声称这是出于政治动机；不过，他在接受美国媒体采访时声称，他此举并非为了避免被弹劾，而且他在几天前就已经计划好了。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>厄瓜多尔官员声称，他最初推迟解散行动是因为他想确保国际象棋比赛得到该国军方的支持。</p><p>值得注意的是，拉索还在受审的第一天，也是唯一一天警告国民议会，如果他认为国民议会有足够票数弹劾他，他将援引克鲁扎达之死。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美媒称，情报官员称，拉索收到情报称，反对派将没有足够的票数，但在弹劾审判前的投票中，反对派似乎在这个问题上有足够的团结，还有余票。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “最根本的是为这场政治危机提供出口，”拉索在接受采访时说。他还声称他的决定是“对国家的慷慨之举，缩短总统任期以实现厄瓜多尔人的共同利益……而不是看到政治家之间争斗的尴尬场面。” </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110475449" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/ecuadors-president-says-he-wont-seek-reelection-after-disbanding-legislature-1110475449.html?share-block=1110475457" data-title="“What was fundamental was to provide an exit to this political crisis,” Lasso said in the interview. He also claimed his decision was an “act of generosity for the country, to shorten a presidential term to achieve the common interest of Ecuadorians… and not see this embarrassing spectacle of fighting between politicians.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">但来自厄瓜多尔的政治学家西蒙帕查诺在接受美国媒体采访时辩称，拉索做出避免弹劾的决定，并推测他决定不参选是因为他知道自己会输。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “在我看来，他没有获胜的机会，”帕查诺说。 “我认为他是一位技术娴熟的扑克玩家。他从不表露情绪。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110475449" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/ecuadors-president-says-he-wont-seek-reelection-after-disbanding-legislature-1110475449.html?share-block=1110475459" data-title="“It seems to me that he has no chance of winning,” Pachano said. “I think he’s a sort of skilled poker player. He never shows emotions.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">厄瓜多尔宪法法院周四支持他的举动，拒绝审理几起旨在阻止国民议会解散的诉讼。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">反对派联盟牢牢控制了国民议会，阻止了拉索制定他的议程，这一事态发展显然令总统感到沮丧，他接着表示，未来的总统不应回避采取同样的举措。 <strong>“我会把它推荐给未来的厄瓜多尔总统，”他说。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">尽管说他不在乎谁接替他的位置，但拉索表示他的创造机会党将竞选一名候选人，但没有说明可能是谁。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">科雷亚周三称解散国民议会违宪，但也表示这是一个夺回国家的机会。周五，他继续号召厄瓜多尔人通过投票改变国家的想法。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “你知道吗？尽管他撒谎和自相矛盾，但拉索是对的：我们正在经历内部骚动，”科雷亚说，同时<a href="https://twitter.com/MashiRafael/status/1659286480986992644" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">引用周四在厄瓜多尔发生的大规模枪击事件的推特</a>视频。 “让我们去参加那些选举，并在投票中横扫他们。” </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110475449" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/ecuadors-president-says-he-wont-seek-reelection-after-disbanding-legislature-1110475449.html?share-block=1110475464" data-title="“You know what? Despite his lies and contradictions, Lasso is right: we are experiencing internal commotion,” Correa said, while quote tweeting videos of the aftermath of a mass shooting event that took place in Ecuador on Thursday. “Let&amp;#x27;s go to those elections and sweep them at the polls.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">科雷亚推测，厄瓜多尔的政治右翼可能会将目光投向前副总统奥托·索南霍尔兹纳 (Otto Sonnenholzner)，他在 2021 年签署了马德里宪章，这是一份谴责社会主义和共产主义的文件。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> <strong>“希望我们不要再上当了，”科雷亚说。</strong></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 04:05:33 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/ecuadors-president-says-he-wont-seek-reelection-after-disbanding-legislature-1110475449.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/ecuadors-president-says-he-wont-seek-reelection-after-disbanding-legislature-1110475449.html<category>美洲</category><category>吉列尔莫·拉索</category><category>拉斐尔科雷亚</category><category>国会</category><category>厄瓜多尔</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists Reveal Time of Oldest Recorded Kisses in History]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110475292" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/06/1083317088_0:0:2047:2275_1440x900_80_0_1_3dba01625d01a65e50a4eac38299c0f9.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1083317037" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/scientists-reveal-time-of-oldest-recorded-kisses-in-history-1110475292.html?share-img=1083317037"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / Dieter Nagl</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">Пара целуется на фоне картины Γустав Климта &quot;Поцелуй&quot; в Вене</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="Пара целуется на фоне картины Густав Климта Поцелуй в Вене  - Sputnik International, 1920, 20.05.2023" title="Пара целуется на фоне картины Густав Климта Поцелуй в Вене" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/06/1083317088_0:796:2048:1947_1920x0_80_0_0_9bfd255a96b5b26ac9a36240d06f79de.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/06/1083317088_0:796:2048:1947_640x0_80_0_0_1422b51edf053aa066ec229df3f58d49.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/06/1083317088_0:796:2048:1947_1280x0_80_0_0_0862f885f0104b9c6e1622116efa8588.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/06/1083317088_0:796:2048:1947_1920x0_80_0_0_9bfd255a96b5b26ac9a36240d06f79de.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / Dieter Nagl </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">叶戈尔·沙波瓦洛夫</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_shapovalov_egor/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a><a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:e.shapovalov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">哥本哈根大学的科学家发现了人类之间浪漫接吻的最早证据。在大约公元前 2500 年的古代文献中提到了它们。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">新发表的研究结果揭示了研究人员如何确定最早提到浪漫接吻的时间可以追溯到大约 4500 年前——大约比印度历史文献详细记载早 1000 年。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">丹麦学者​​在研究美索不达米亚的粘土片后做出了他们的重大发现，其中提到亲吻嘴唇是性游戏的一部分。这些泥板早于青铜时代的印度手稿，可追溯到公元前 1500 年左右，最初被认为包括第一次这样的提及。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">研究人员指出，在现存最早的苏美尔语和阿卡德语文献之一中发现了对接吻的描述，这些文献在美索不达米亚使用。文字被认为起源于公元前 3200 年左右的现代伊拉克。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “在古代美索不达米亚，这是存在于今伊拉克和叙利亚幼发拉底河和底格里斯河之间的早期人类文化的名称，人们在粘土板上用楔形文字 [楔形标记] 书写......它们包含清楚的例子表明接吻在古代被认为是浪漫亲密关系的一部分，就像......友谊和家庭成员关系的一部分，“Troels Pank Arbøll 博士说，他是美索不达米亚大学医学史专家。丹麦哥本哈根。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110475292" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/scientists-reveal-time-of-oldest-recorded-kisses-in-history-1110475292.html?share-block=1110475296" data-title="&amp;quot;In ancient Mesopotamia, which is the name for the early human cultures that existed between the Euphrates and Tigris rivers in present-day Iraq and Syria, people wrote in cuneiform script [wedge-shaped marks] on clay tablets... and they contain clear examples that kissing was considered a part of romantic intimacy in ancient times, just as... part of friendships and family members’ relations,&amp;quot; said Dr. Troels Pank Arbøll, an expert on the history of medicine in Mesopotamia at the University of Copenhagen in Denmark."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在可追溯到公元前 2500 年（即文字出现后约 700 年）的文本中，提到了接吻，这显然分为两组：第一组表示友谊或亲情，另一个 - 是纯粹的色情行为。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">研究资料表明，与性、家庭和友谊有关的接吻是公元前 3 千年末古代近东中部地区日常生活的常见部分，而且很可能不仅仅是该地区的特征。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “因此，接吻不应被视为一种仅起源于任何单一地区并从那里传播的习俗，而是似乎在几千年的时间里在多种古代文化中都有这种习俗，”Troels 补充道。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110475292" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/scientists-reveal-time-of-oldest-recorded-kisses-in-history-1110475292.html?share-block=1110475300" data-title="&amp;quot;Therefore, kissing should not be regarded as a custom that originated exclusively in any single region and spread from there but rather appears to have been practiced in multiple ancient cultures over several millennia,&amp;quot; added Troels."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">而且，甚至在当时人类就猜测，通过接吻，人们可以“交换”各种感染和病毒。古代近东文献提到了对“bubutu”或“bushanu”等疾病的描述，这些疾病可被识别为现代疱疹。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该研究的结果发表在<a href="https://doi.org/10.1126/science.adf0512" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">《科学》</a>杂志上。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 03:52:03 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/scientists-reveal-time-of-oldest-recorded-kisses-in-history-1110475292.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/scientists-reveal-time-of-oldest-recorded-kisses-in-history-1110475292.html<category>超越政治</category><category>科学与技术</category><category>哥本哈根大学</category><category>吻</category><category>历史</category><category>古代历史</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Russian Envoy to US: Emerging Economies to Turn Backs on Washington Due to Sanctions’ Harm]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110474980" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/0a/0d/1101821706_0:0:2784:2047_1440x900_80_0_1_2b46821082956b14b229a5ca2780e8bf.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1101821689" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/antonov-emerging-economies-to-turn-backs-on-washington-due-to-sanctions-harm-1110474980.html?share-img=1101821689"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Grigory Sysoev</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">俄罗斯驻美国大使阿纳托利·安东诺夫</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="Russian Ambassador to the United States Anatoly Antonov - Sputnik International, 1920, 20.05.2023" title="俄罗斯驻美国大使阿纳托利·安东诺夫" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/0a/0d/1101821706_0:241:2784:1807_1920x0_80_0_0_56c27145eb18b5d62f122af102cadb4f.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/0a/0d/1101821706_0:241:2784:1807_640x0_80_0_0_1de763f52932ec9e3bc77ccc0102af52.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/0a/0d/1101821706_0:241:2784:1807_1280x0_80_0_0_42fc2e289f0b563e7f4d9ce4eabea6e6.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/0a/0d/1101821706_0:241:2784:1807_1920x0_80_0_0_56c27145eb18b5d62f122af102cadb4f.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / Grigory Sysoev</div> / </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据华盛顿（人造卫星）网报道：俄罗斯驻美国大使阿纳托利·安东诺夫表示，新兴经济体将了解华盛顿目前的制裁政策对其切身利益的危害，并将远离美国。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “[美国]政府难道不明白，它的步骤正在损害自己的长期目标吗？显然，新兴经济体会看到美国的政策对它们的切身利益造成的伤害，并将背弃它们在华盛顿，”安东诺夫在俄罗斯外交使团电报频道上对记者发表的评论中说。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位大使说，新的一揽子制裁重申了已经做过的事情，并没有包含任何真正的新措施，并补充说华盛顿的意图是试图吓跑俄罗斯市场的合作伙伴。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “混淆商界、专家和公众。让他们相信我们处于某种‘限制上限’之下。”当然，这远非事实，”他说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110474980" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/antonov-emerging-economies-to-turn-backs-on-washington-due-to-sanctions-harm-1110474980.html?share-block=1110474983" data-title="&quot;To confuse the business circles, experts and the public. Convince them that we are under some kind of ‘cap of restrictions.’ Of course, this is far from being true,&quot; he said. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “俄罗斯，不是在口头上，而是在行动上，证明了它有能力应对阻止其进步、迫使其放弃其基本原则的企图。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">周五，美国财政部和国务院宣布对 300 多人实施新的大规模一揽子与俄罗斯相关的制裁，其中包括 46 名个人、20 多个国家的数百个实体以及数十架飞机和船只。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 02:56:20 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/antonov-emerging-economies-to-turn-backs-on-washington-due-to-sanctions-harm-1110474980.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/antonov-emerging-economies-to-turn-backs-on-washington-due-to-sanctions-harm-1110474980.html<category>世界</category><category>阿纳托利·安东诺夫</category><category>华盛顿</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>金库</category><category>制裁</category><category>乌克兰危机</category><category>俄罗斯经济受到制裁</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Magnitude 7.1 Earthquake Occurs off New Caledonia Coast - USGS]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110474849" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106201/08/1062010880_0:0:3000:1968_1440x900_80_0_1_c8264c9a5026fa3f3a7852585d7cc562.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1062010879" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/magnitude-71-earthquake-occurs-off-new-caledonia-coast---usgs-1110474849.html?share-img=1062010879"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© 美联社照片/</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">地震仪</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="Seismograph  - Sputnik International, 1920, 20.05.2023" title="地震仪" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106201/08/1062010880_0:140:3000:1828_1920x0_80_0_0_e5ac01813c4ac686cbb190a48b997d02.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106201/08/1062010880_0:140:3000:1828_640x0_80_0_0_49a8e96d6122dda7be043b9efc9180a4.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106201/08/1062010880_0:140:3000:1828_1280x0_80_0_0_aca979e806efd9b1eab6aa5dce6898da.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106201/08/1062010880_0:140:3000:1828_1920x0_80_0_0_e5ac01813c4ac686cbb190a48b997d02.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据莫斯科（人造卫星）网报道：据美国地质调查局（USGS）报道，新喀里多尼亚海岸发生了 7.1 级地震。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国地质勘探局称，周六格林威治标准时间 01:51，地震发生在新喀里多尼亚首都努美阿西北约 261 英里处，震源深度约为 22 英里（36 公里）。在降级为 7.1 之前，它最初的震级为 7.4。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在最初的地震发生近 20 分钟后，记录到一次 6.5 级余震。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>监测人员警告说，地震震中 300 公里以内的海岸可能会发生海啸。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">目前，还没有任何损坏或人员伤亡的报告。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">最近一次是在周五早些时候沿新喀里多尼亚海岸线记录到强烈的 7.7 级地震之后发生的，两次余震分别为 5.9 级和 5.4 级。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 02:40:41 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/magnitude-71-earthquake-occurs-off-new-caledonia-coast---usgs-1110474849.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/magnitude-71-earthquake-occurs-off-new-caledonia-coast---usgs-1110474849.html<category>世界</category><category>新喀里多尼亚</category><category>美国地质调查局 (USGS)</category><category>美国地质调查局</category><category>地震</category><category>海啸警报</category></item></channel></rss>